# Follow design markdown

When any `DESIGN.md` or `design.md` exists in the repository, treat it as binding for UI and product work.

## Discovery

- Check the project root first. If the task touches a subtree, also check the nearest ancestor `DESIGN.md` or `design.md`.
- If multiple files apply, use the nearest ancestor for the files being changed. Parent docs supply shared defaults; child docs may add scope-specific rules. Do not drop explicit don'ts from any applicable file.

## Before UI work

Read the applicable design markdown before proposing or implementing UI, styling, layout, motion, component patterns, or art direction.

## Compliance

- Follow declared tokens, patterns, constraints, accessibility requirements, and don'ts strictly unless the user explicitly overrides a rule.
- Do not substitute nearby palettes, type genres, spacing rhythms, or motion levels that are not in the document.
- When the document defines fallbacks or progressive enhancement, implement those paths; do not make decorative layers required for core use.
- Prefer referencing the file by path over paraphrasing from memory.

## When absent

If no design markdown file is present, do not invent a design system or visual language for the repo.
